header: Mariam has insurance that covers "Escape of Oil." In an "Escape of Oil" event,
policy_wording: An incident that occurs with a fixed heating installation that leaks oil results in damage to the policyholder's property.

continuation: Denise is moving to a new home on the other side of town. She asks her uncle, a retired professional mover, to help move her belongings out of her current home. During the move, her uncle's truck is involved in a minor accident that damages several pieces of her furniture and other belongings. Denise files a claim with her insurance company for the damage to her belongings.
header: Denise has insurance that covers "House Removal." In a "House Removal" event,
policy_wording: An incident occurs with policyholder belongings that are moved by professional contractors.This incident results in damage to those belongings.

continuation: Late one night, Joanne hears loud crashing noises coming from another room in her home and believes that a burglar has broken in. From her bedroom, she frantically calls the police, who make a forced entry into her home to assess the situation. It turns out that the noises Joanne heard were indeed from a burglar, whom the police promptly arrest. Joanne files a claim with her insurance company for the damage caused by the forced entry.
header: Joanne has insurance that covers "Emergency Damages." In an "Emergency Damages" event,
policy_wording: An incident occurs with first responders who make a forced home entry.This incident results in damage to the policyholder's property.

continuation: Aneesh drives a convertible Porsche and parks his car one day in an outdoor parking lot. While his car is parked in the lot, a baseball from a nearby little league game hits one of his car's side mirrors. When he returns, he discovers that the side mirror has been severely damaged and that broken shards from the side mirror managed to leave scratches on the car. Aneesh files a claim with his insurance company for the damage.
header: Aneesh has insurance that covers "Vehicle Glass Damage." In a "Vehicle Glass Damage" event,
policy_wording: An incident occurs with an external force that breaks vehicle glass.This incident results in damage to the body work of the policyholder's vehicle.

continuation: Beth lives in a very quiet neighborhood at the edge of town with her two young children. Upon returning home from work one day, she sees that an exterior wall of her house is covered in graffiti. She reviews her home surveillance footage and sees that a group of neighborhood teenagers spraypainted the wall. She hires professional painters to paint over the graffiti. Beth files a claim with her insurance company for the damages.
header: Beth has insurance that covers "Malicious Acts or Vandalism." In a "Malicious Acts or Vandalism" event,
policy_wording: An incident occurs with a colorant or stain that is wielded by an adverse third party.This incident results in damage to the policyholder's property.

continuation: One day, Gwen drives her SUV to the grocery store. After buying groceries, she injures her wrist when she lifts a heavy grocery bag into her car. This incident ultimately leads to thousands of dollars in medical expenses. Gwen files a claim with her insurance company for the damages.
header: Gwen has insurance that covers a "Personal Accident." In a "Personal Accident" event,
policy_wording: An incident occurs with a policyholder who is injured by a vehicular collision.This incident results in substantial damage to the policyholder's person.

continuation: One evening, several of Blake's friends crowd into his house for a dance party. The many rambunctious dancers cause Blake's house to shake, which damages the house's foundation. Blake files a claim with his insurance company for the damage.
header: Blake has home insurance that covers "Ground Heave." In a "Ground Heave" event,
policy_wording: An incident that occurs with ground movement or landslip that is induced by an external force results in damage to the policyholder's property.

continuation: One day, a lightning storm passes through Cam's neighborhood and lightning hits his roof, causing a fire. Almost all of his roof burns before firefighters manage to extinguish it. Cam files a claim with his insurance company for the damage.
header: Cam has insurance that covers "Storm Damage." In a "Storm Damage" event,
policy_wording: An incident that occurs with lightning that is created by a storm results in damage to the policyholder's property.

continuation: Gavin works as an A/C repair technician in a small town. One day, Gavin is off from work and decides to put holiday lights up on his roof. Because Gavin is an experienced repairman, he figures he doesn't need a ladder to get onto his roof and decides to free climb the exterior wall of his house instead. While climbing the wall, Gavin loses his balance and falls, causing significant injury. Because of this, he subsequently has to stop working for weeks. Gavin files a claim with his insurance company for lost income.
header: Gavin has insurance that covers "General Damages." In a "General Damages'' event,
policy_wording: An incident occurs with a workplace hazard that injures a policyholder.This incident results in missed employment for the policyholder.

continuation: One day, Ken parks his car next to his home, and while he is out on a jog his neighbor's home catches fire. The fire spreads to Ken's car, which is subsequently destroyed in the blaze. Ken files a claim with his insurance company for the damage.
header: Ken has insurance that covers "Vehicle Fire." In a "Vehicle Fire" event,
policy_wording: An incident that occurs with an external force that instigates a fire or explosion results in damage to the policyholder's vehicle.

continuation: Carol's bathroom wall has become severely damaged due to a pipe that leaked for several hours before Carol managed to find a plumber who could fix the leak. Carol files a claim with her insurance company for the damage to her wall.
header: Carol has insurance that covers "Escape of Water." In an "Escape of Water'' event,
policy_wording: An incident that occurs with water that is released by an internal source in an abrupt and unexpected manner results in damage to the policyholder's property.

continuation: Justin, a professional plumber, is repairing his leaky kitchen sink when he inadvertently punctures a pipe that leads to the kitchen. In order to access and repair the damaged pipe, Justin has to tear out drywall and tear up floorboards. He files a claim with his insurance company for the damage.
header: Justin has insurance that covers "Trace and Access." In a "Trace and Access" event,
policy_wording: An incident that occurs with a skilled professional who accesses cables or pipes under reasonable circumstances results in damage to the policyholder's property.
